th tf.device('/cpu:0'):</code> around the model construction.</p>", "body_text": "I would find it convenient to be able to start a session in cpu only mode (e. g. because you have another session running already that hogs all the VRAM). My workaround for now is to use\ngpu_options = tf.GPUOptions(per_process_gpu_memory_fraction=0.01)\nwith tf.Session(config=tf.ConfigProto(log_device_placement=True, gpu_options=gpu_options)) as sess:\n\nAnd then wrap with tf.device('/cpu:0'): around the model construction.", "body": "I would find it convenient to be able to start a session in cpu only mode (e. g. because you have another session running already that hogs all the VRAM). My workaround for now is to use\n\n```\ngpu_options = tf.GPUOptions(per_process_gpu_memory_fraction=0.01)\nwith tf.Session(config=tf.ConfigProto(log_device_placement=True, gpu_options=gpu_options)) as sess:\n```\n\nAnd then wrap `with tf.device('/cpu:0'):` around the model construction.\n"}